{"label":"Lines and Angles","id":"line-angle-6","list":[{"id":"slide","type":"slides2","label":"Slides: Lines & Angles","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Lines & Angles","displayType":"steps","images":"img/math/big/lines-angles-6","imgHeight":400,"fontSize":"1.5rem","steps":[{"text":"A point determines a location. It is denoted by a capital letter. It is a 'dot' with minimum possible size. eg: tip of a compass, sharpened end of a pencil, pointed end of a needle.","img":"point"},{"text":"A Line Segment is the shortest distance between two points. Here, the points A and B are called the end points of the line segment","img":"line-segment"},{"text":"Line: If we extend a line segments on both sides, we get a model line. A line goes endlessly on both sides. As we cannot draw endless line, we add arrows at the two ends.","img":"line"},{"text":"A ray is a portion of a line that starts at one point (classed starting or initial point), and goes on endlessly in a direction.","img":"ray"},{"text":"This image has 5 points, and 4 line segments connecting the points. The line segments are LM, MP, PQ, QR. They can also be represented as RQ, QP, PM, ML","img":"line-segments-list"},{"text":"An angle is formed by two rays having a common starting point. The meeting point of the two rays is called 'vertex', and the rays are called 'arms'.","img":"angle"},{"text":"The size of an angle is the amount of rotation or turn that is needed about the vertex to move the first ray to the second ray. ","img":"angle-create"},{"text":"If the angle is between 0° and 90°, it is called acute angle. If the angle measures exactly 90°, it is called right angle. If the angle is between 90° and 180°, it is called obtuse angle.","img":"angle-types"},{"text":"If the angle is between 180° and 360°, we called it as 'reflex angle'. It is because another angle (obtuse or acute or right angle) is formed at the other side of the vertex.","img":"reflex-angle"},{"text":"If a circle is divided into equal number of parts, then the angle is also divided equally among them.","img":"angles-by-splitting-circle"}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"pic","label":"Answer the question based on the image.","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Answer the question based on the image.","type":"image","image":"math/big/lines-angles-6/angleWithProtractor","questions":[{"qText":"The angle POQ is ______ angle.","options":"an acute, an obtuse, a right"},{"qText":"The angle POR is ______ angle.","options":"an obtuse, a right, an acute"},{"qText":"The angle QOS is ______ angle.","options":"a right, an obtuse, an acute"},{"qText":"The angle QOT is ______ angle.","options":"an obtuse, a right, an acute"},{"qText":"The angle UOS is ______ angle.","options":"an acute, a right, an obtuse"},{"qText":"How much does the angle POQ measure?","type":"number","value":35},{"qText":"How much does the angle POR measure?","type":"number","value":95},{"qText":"How much does the angle UOR measure?","type":"number","value":85},{"qText":"How much does the angle UOS measure?","type":"number","value":55},{"qText":"How much does the angle TOR measure?","type":"number","value":65}]}},{"type":"geometry","label":"Draw Lines","id":"lines","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"isBigScreen":true},"data":["Draw a line of length 4 cm. | line | 4\nDraw a line of length 2.6 cm. | line | 2.6\nDraw a line of length 3 cm. | line | 3\nDraw a line of length 3.6 cm. | line | 3.6\nDraw a line of length 2.4 cm. | line | 2.4",{"scale":50,"leastCount":10,"unit":"m","text":"Draw a line of length 300 m. | line | 300\nDraw a line of length 450 m. | line | 450\nDraw a line of length 600 m. | line | 600\nDraw a line of length 510 m. | line | 510\nDraw a line of length 490 m. | line | 490"},{"scale":0.25,"leastCount":0.1,"unit":"km","text":"Draw a line of length 2 km. | line | 2\nDraw a line of length 1.1 km. | line | 1.1\nDraw a line of length 1.6 km. | line | 1.6\nDraw a line of length 2.3 km. | line | 2.3\nDraw a line of length 0.9 km. | line | 0.9"}]},{"type":"geometryType","label":"Right, Acute, Obtuse angles","id":"angle-type","data":{"type":"angle"}},{"type":"geometry","label":"Make the Angles","id":"700","onlyBigScreen":true,"commonData":{"isBigScreen":true},"data":["Make an angle of 60 degree. | angle | 60\nMake an angle of 180 degree. | angle | 180\nMake an angle of 45 degree. | angle | 45\nMake an angle of 135 degree. | angle | 135\nMake an angle of 75 degree. | angle | 75","Make an angle of 50 degree. | angle | 50\nMake an angle of 170 degree. | angle | 170\nMake an angle of 270 degree. | angle | 270\nMake an angle of 65 degree. | angle | 65\nMake an angle of 300 degree. | angle | 300","Make an angle of 200 degree. | angle | 200\nMake an angle of 100 degree. | angle | 100\nMake an angle of 225 degree. | angle | 225\nMake an angle of 320 degree. | angle | 320\nMake an angle of 250 degree. | angle | 250"]}]}